        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): add unsend action handler using im.message.delete (recall API)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThe Feishu plugin registered message actions (send, read, edit, etc.) but did not handle the `unsend` action, causing `\"Unsupported Feishu action: unsend\"` errors when agents attempted to recall sent messages.\n\nThe Feishu/Lark SDK maps `client.im.message.delete()` to the recall endpoint (`DELETE /open-apis/im/v1/messages/{message_id}`). Despite the method name, this IS the recall/unsend API that removes the message for all participants. There is no separate `recall()` method on the raw SDK client.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/feishu/src/channel.ts`: Add `\"unsend\"` to advertised actions set; add unsend handler using `client.im.message.delete()` (the Feishu recall API)\n- `extensions/feishu/src/channel.test.ts`: Add test for unsend action; update 3 action-list assertions to include `\"unsend\"`\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: Feishu unsend action throws \"Unsupported Feishu action\" instead of recalling the message via the Lark SDK\nReal environment tested: macOS 15.5, Node 22.19, local vitest via node scripts/run-vitest.mjs\nExact steps or command run after this patch: node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/feishu/src/channel.test.ts\nEvidence after fix: terminal output copied below.\n\n### Unit test proof\n\n```console\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/feishu/src/channel.test.ts\n ✓ extensions/feishu/src/channel.test.ts (55 tests) 89ms\n   ✓ feishu channel actions > unsends (recalls) messages via im.message.delete\n   ✓ feishu channel actions > advertises the expanded Feishu action surface\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  55 passed (55)\n```\n\n### SDK dependency-contract proof\n\nFull method inventory of `@larksuiteoapi/node-sdk@1.64.0` confirms `delete` exists and `recall` does not:\n\n```console\n$ node -e \"const L=require('@larksuiteoapi/node-sdk');const c=new L.Client({appId:'x',appSecret:'x'});\n  console.log('SDK version:', require('@larksuiteoapi/node-sdk/package.json').version);\n  console.log('im.message.delete exists:', typeof c.im.message.delete === 'function');\n  console.log('im.message.recall exists:', typeof c.im.message.recall);\n  for (const k of Object.getOwnPropertyNames(c.im.message))\n    if (typeof c.im.message[k]==='function' && k!=='constructor') console.log(' ',k);\"\n\nSDK version: 1.64.0\nim.message.delete exists: true\nim.message.recall exists: undefined\n  create\n  delete\n  forward\n  get\n  listWithIterator\n  list\n  mergeForward\n  patch\n  pushFollowUp\n  readUsers\n  reply\n  update\n  urgentApp\n  urgentPhone\n  urgentSms\n  createByCard\n  replyByCard\n  updateByCard\n```\n\nThe handler calls `client.im.message.delete({ path: { message_id } })` which maps to `DELETE /open-apis/im/v1/messages/{message_id}` per the [Feishu API reference](https://open.feishu.cn/document/server-docs/im-v1/message/delete). The SDK does not expose a `recall` method; `delete` is the only way to recall a message.\n\nObserved result after fix: unsend handler calls `client.im.message.delete({path:{message_id}})` and returns `{ok:true, action:\"unsend\", messageId}`.\nWhat was not tested: Live Feishu bot message recall (requires Feishu app credentials with `im:message` scope and a real Feishu workspace). No Feishu workspace is available in this environment.\n\nCloses #85587\n",
        "branch": "fix/feishu-unsend-recall-api",
